    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We presented an initial pilot study report focused on immunogenicity and safety following an inactivated whole-virus severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 vaccination among kidney transplant (KT) recipients. At four weeks after the first dose of vaccine, the level of anti\u2013receptor-binding domain IgG antibody was not significantly different compared to before vaccination in 30 KT recipients (p = 0.45). Moreover, a significant lower mean (95% CI) anti\u2013receptor-binding domain IgG antibody was observed compared to 30 immunocompetent controls (2.4 [95% CI 1.3-3.5] vs. 173.1 [95% CI 88.3-2,457.9] AU/mL, p &lt; 0.001). Mild adverse events included fever (17%) and localized pain at the injection site (14%) were observed after vaccination.</jats:p>",
